      • Interval

        public Interval(T minimum,
                T maximum,
                Interval.Rule minimumRule,
                Interval.Rule maximumRule)
         throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a new instance.
        Parameters:
        minimum - The minimum value.
        maximum - The maximum value.
        minimumRule - The rule for the minimum bound; can be null .
        If null will be set to Rule.INCLUSIVE.
        maximumRule - The rule for the maximum bound; can be null .
        If null will be set to Rule.INCLUSIVE.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If either minimum or maximum is null or if the specified interval is invalid.
        Typically, an invalid interval may be ]x, x[, [x, x[ or ]x, x].
        Since:
        1.1

        public static double project(Number number,
                             Interval<? extends Number> source,
                             Interval<? extends Number> destination)
                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Project interval [source] on interval [destination] ands return the image of the given value.
        Parameters:
        number - The value to be projected.
        source - The source interval (value must be contained within the interval).
        destination - The destination interval.
        Returns:
        The image of the given value after the projection.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If value, source or destination is null or if source has a range of 0.

      • project

        public static double project(double value,
                             double inMin,
                             double inMax,
                             double outMin,
                             double outMax)
                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Project interval [inMin, inMax] on interval [outMin, outMax] and return the image of the given value.
        This method does not create new Interval objects.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to be projected.
        inMin - The source minimum.
        inMax - The source maximum.
        outMin - The destination minimum.
        outMax - the destination maximum.
        Returns:
        The image of the given value after the projection.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the source interval has a range of 0.
